The White House has issued a statement expressing concern over the detention of members of the Damas de Blanco in Havana. The statement highlights the Cuban authorities' disregard for the rights of the Cuban people and calls for the immediate release of those detained. It also urges Cuban authorities to stop using intimidation and harassment to suppress peaceful dissent. The statement emphasizes President Obama and the American people's support for the Damas de Blanco and other voices in Cuban civil society who advocate for the freedom of the Cuban people to determine their country's future.